= Math Formulas

The Euler's identity: $e^(i pi) + 1 = 0$

The quadratic formula: $x = (-b plus.minus sqrt(b^2 - 4a c)) / (2a)$

== Integral and Sum

$ integral_0^infinity e^(-x^2) dif x = sqrt(pi) / 2 $

$ sum_(n=1)^infinity 1/n^2 = pi^2 / 6 $

== Matrix

$ mat(1, 2, 3; 4, 5, 6; 7, 8, 9) $
